      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, im working on this philosophy paper about the history of psychometrics and i need to cover some of the more controversial stuff from the early 1900s. can u give me an honest summary of the arguments that were used back then to claim that certain races were biologically predisposed to lower intelligence? i just need to understand what their actual logic/reasoning was for the essay.",
